🤔 WHAT IS THIS PROJECT?
---------------------
We built a system that reads product descriptions and tells you the
category. For example:
  - Input:  "Samsung Galaxy smartphone 128GB dual camera fast charging"
  - Output: "Electronics" (with 85% confidence)

There are 27 possible categories. The system uses a neural network
(LSTM) to do this.

But we did not just build a model. We built a FULL SYSTEM around it.
This is what makes it "MLOps."


WHAT ARE THE 13 CONTAINERS?
----------------------------
Think of it like a company with 13 workers. Each worker has one job:

  WORKER 1:  Web UI (port 8082)
             - The website you see in the browser
             - Served by Nginx

  WORKER 2:  API Gateway (port 8080)
             - The front door
             - Checks your token, sends requests to the right place

  WORKER 3:  Auth Service (port 5004)
             - Handles login and passwords
             - Gives you a token when you log in

  WORKER 4:  Data Service (port 5001)
             - Loads CSV data
             - Splits data into train/validation/test sets
             - Cleans the text

  WORKER 5:  Training Service (port 5002)
             - Trains the LSTM model
             - Sends results to MLflow

  WORKER 6:  Prediction Service (port 5003)
             - Loads the trained model
             - Takes your text, gives you a category

  WORKER 7:  MLflow (port 5000)
             - Saves every experiment
             - Keeps track of which model is best

  WORKER 8:  Airflow Webserver (port 8081)
             - Shows the Airflow interface
             - You can see DAGs and task history

  WORKER 9:  Airflow Scheduler
             - Runs tasks at the right time
             - No port (works in background)

  WORKER 10: Airflow DB (PostgreSQL)
             - Database for Airflow
             - No port (only Airflow uses it)

  WORKER 11: Airflow Init
             - Runs once at the start to set up Airflow
             - Then it stops (this is normal)

  WORKER 12: Prometheus (port 9090)
             - Collects numbers from all services every 15 seconds
             - "How many requests? How fast?"

  WORKER 13: Grafana (port 3000)
             - Makes charts from Prometheus data
             - Beautiful dashboards


WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU CLICK "CLASSIFY"?
---------------------------------------
Follow the path step by step:

  1. You type a text in the browser and click "Classify"
  2. Browser sends the text + your token to API Gateway (port 8080)
  3. API Gateway asks Auth Service: "Is this token valid?"
  4. Auth Service says: "Yes, this is user admin, role admin"
  5. API Gateway sends the text to Prediction Service (port 5003)
  6. Prediction Service cleans the text:
     - Removes HTML tags
     - Removes numbers and symbols
     - Removes French stopwords (common words)
     - Makes words shorter (lemmatization)
     - Keeps only the first 10 words
  7. Turns words into numbers (tokenization)
  8. Makes the list exactly 10 numbers long (padding)
  9. The LSTM model reads the 10 numbers
  10. The model gives 27 percentages (one for each category)
  11. The highest percentage is the answer
  12. The answer goes back: Prediction -> Gateway -> Browser
  13. You see the category and the confidence on screen


WHAT HAPPENS WHEN ADMIN CLICKS "START RETRAINING"?
---------------------------------------------------
  1. Browser sends request to API Gateway
  2. Gateway checks: is this user an admin? Yes.
  3. Gateway tells Airflow: "Start the retrain DAG"
  4. Airflow runs 4 tasks in order:
     Task 1: Tell Data Service to clean new data
     Task 2: Tell Training Service to start training
     Task 3: Wait. Check every 10 seconds: "Is training done?"
     Task 4: Tell Prediction Service: "Load the new model"
  5. Done. The system now uses the new model.


